cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 75 mi WNW of Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic
cyclone.trajectory: Continuing west-northwest across Hispaniola, forecast to move near the Turks & Caicos and SE Bahamas Thursday, skirt or cross north-central Cuba Friday, then curve into the eastern Gulf of Mexico toward the northern Gulf Coast late weekend
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: northern Gulf Coast (near the FL-AL border)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Northern coast of Haiti, Turks & Caicos Islands, southeastern Bahamas, and the Cuban provinces of Ciego de Avila eastward through Guantanamo under Tropical Storm Watch
weather_observation.warning_coast: Dominican Republic south coast from Punta Palenque eastward and north coast from the DR/Haiti border eastward under Tropical Storm Warning
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Hispaniola, Turks & Caicos, southeastern and central Bahamas, northern coast of Cuba, and the northern Gulf Coast later this weekend
